Description: This is a Fender Squire Vintage Modified Stratocaster. The serial # is NHS 1002373 this is a hard to fine limited run made in India. a beautiful metallic Gun Metal Gray. heavier weight than you average squire. Fender vintage style bent metal saddles, Squire "Fender" neck plate, clean aged white pickguard, S/S/H Duncan Designed pickups, black humbucker. black and gold Fender logo. the body has one small chip as shown in the photo. the rest of the body has no damage or marks. the neck is perfect! The hard maple/rosewood vintage tint neck is great. no fret wear, sealed tuners. she appears to be all original. good strings, very low action. truss rod is fine. set up, cleaned and polished. smoke and pet free home, sounds great. This is a 2010 Made in India Squier Vintage Modified HSS Strat - They stopped production in India after 2011 and started in 2007 25.5" Scale tinted maple neck, 9.5" radius, rosewood fretboard, 21 frets Duncan Designed SC-102 Stack middle and neck pickups Duncan Designed HB-112B which is modelled after the Seymour Duncan "SCREAMIN DEAMON" pickup. The middle and neck pickups are stack noiseless single coils. The Vintage Modified Strat HSS incorporates the chop-shop look with a hot output, black bobbin humbucking pickup slammed into the traditional Stratocaster platform. Other features include a High gloss-finished Tinted maple neck and two Duncan Designed Stack for Strat pickups (neck and middle) and one HB-112 B humbucker in the bridge position.
